              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 Intense Neutron Generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three targets (UO2(NO3)2 powder of 99% or more purity)",
                "and monitors (aluminum foil of 99.99% purity, 0.05 mm",
                "thick) were made into circular disks with diameters of",
                "13.4 mm, 13.8 mm and 14.4 mm respectively.",
                "The thickness of the UO2(NO3)2 samples were 4.3 mm,",
                "4.5 mm and 5.4 mm, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Au-Si surface barrier detector used at",
                "135 deg, accompanying the alpha-particle tube, was at",
                "a distance of 110 cm from the target."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A coaxial GMX60 HPGe detector (ORTEC, made in",
                "USA) with a relative efficiency of 68% and an energy",
                "resolution of 1.82 keV FWHM at 1.33 MeV. The",
                "calibration of point source efficiency is done by",
                "152Eu,137Cs and 60Co standard point sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three sandwiches of Al-U-Al were mounted",
                "at 0, 45 and 90 deg angles respectively, relative to",
                "the deuteron beam direction and centered about the",
                "tritium-titanium target at distances of 50 mm. In",
                "order to prevent the scattered thermal neutrons, a",
                "cadmium foil was covered the sandwich sample during",
                "the irradiation. The samples were irradiated for 70",
                "min and cooled for about 3 h. The gamma-activities",
                "of the irradiated UO2(NO3)2 and Al samples were",
                "measured off-line."
              ]
            }
          ],
